{% submission %}

{% submission-part type="problem" %}

I have so many students on IEPs or READ plans that need tests read to them, but don't have the personnel to do this in the general Ed classroom. 

{% /submission-part %}

{% submission-part type="proposed-solution" %}

Ideally, this app would house audio recordings of tests/activities. It would be so cool if AI could transcribe, but would be so happy to read and record audio myself. The cover image for each audio recording would be the first page of the test so that students who can't access text would be able to identify which recording to listen to on their own. Oh and let's have content area folders to keep everything organized! It would also be easy to link to Google Classroom so every student who needs it will have it in their own devices and can listen at their own pace. 

{% /submission-part %}

{% /submission %}